 @TKGolfYT I don’t think you need your own robot and there are not a lot of them around even if you wanted to rent one for a day or two. But there is quite a bit of robot testing data out there … the only trick would be matching up the balls off the shelf to those tested by the robot. 

For example, there is some 2023 robot testing data out there, but you’d have to test the compression of the same 2023 balls to match up the data to your compression.

The reality is the manufacturers just don’t want the real numbers out, not because it’s all that proprietary, but probably because we’d all find out that there really isn’t a huge difference …
